PN,31601
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1783982881
OL,3,CMastermind behind E88m Louvre heist
OL,4,Cthought they 'could have stolen more'
OL,6,FThe mastermind of the Louvre heist was
OL,7,Fdisappointed with the E88 million (#75
OL,8,Fmillion) haul and believed the gang
OL,9,Fcould have seized more of France's
OL,10,Fcrown jewels, French media have
OL,11,Freported.
OL,13,FFrench newspaper Le Monde, citing a
OL,14,Ftranscript of a police interview with
OL,15,Ftwo of the thieves, revealed neither
OL,16,Fof them was willing to reveal who
OL,17,Forganised the daring heist, which
OL,18,Fstunned France after more than #75m of
OL,19,Fjewels were stolen from the famous
OL,20,Fmuseum.
OL,26,@kD@SOkoD@WOk
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1783982881
OL,3,CMastermind behind E88m Louvre heist
OL,4,Cthought they 'could have stolen more'
OL,6,FThe newspaper identified the thieves
OL,7,Fas 40-year-old Abdoulaye N, an
OL,8,Funlicensed taxi driver and former
OL,9,Fsocial media star, and 36-year-old
OL,10,FGhelamallah A, an unemployed Algerian
OL,11,Fsuffering from Diogenes syndrome.
OL,13,FThey are currently in custody and are
OL,14,Fsuspected of being the two men who
OL,15,Fbroke into the museum on October 19,
OL,16,F2025.
OL,18,FPolice believe they are the two men
OL,19,Fwho climbed onto the balcony of the
OL,20,Fmuseum with a hired van mounted with a
OL,21,Fladder.
OL,26,@kD@SOk
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1783982881
OL,3,CMastermind behind E88m Louvre heist
OL,4,Cthought they 'could have stolen more'
OL,6,FThey were arrested a week after the
OL,7,Fheist. Le Monde secured transcripts of
OL,8,Findividual interviews with them,
OL,9,Fcarried out in June 2026.
OL,11,FBoth of them said they would not
OL,12,Freveal the identity of the mysterious
OL,13,Fmastermind amid fear of reprisals
OL,14,Fagainst their families.
OL,16,FAbdoulaye N told investigators: "I
OL,17,Fwasn't threatened, but I received
OL,18,Fcalls from outside (while in
OL,19,Fdetention). They told me to keep
OL,20,Fquiet."
OL,26,@kD@SOkzD@Tpm{D@Jpn
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1783982881
OL,3,CMastermind behind E88m Louvre heist
OL,4,Cthought they 'could have stolen more'
OL,6,FDuring their escape, the team split
OL,7,Finto two groups, with Abdoulaye N
OL,8,Fkeeping hold of the jewels and handing
OL,9,Fthem over to the mastermind of the
OL,10,Foperation.
OL,12,FAccording to Abdoulaye N: "The person
OL,13,Fwho ordered the theft wasn't happy. He
OL,14,Fthought we could have taken more. We
OL,15,Fhad wasted time coming back in through
OL,16,Fthe window."
OL,18,FBoth of the suspects say they do not
OL,19,Fknow what has happened to the jewels
OL,20,Fsince
OL,26,@kD@SOk
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1783982881
OL,3,CMastermind behind E88m Louvre heist
OL,4,Cthought they 'could have stolen more'
OL,6,FThey both claimed they were hired just
OL,7,Fa few days before the heist.
OL,9,FAbdoulaye N claimed he was in dire
OL,10,Ffinancial straits and was promised
OL,11,F15,000-20,00 euros for the heist, with
OL,12,Fthe potential for more depending on
OL,13,Fthe amount of valuables they stole.
OL,15,FAbdoulaye N said he was aware he was
OL,16,Fgoing to steal from the Louvre, but
OL,17,FGhelamallah A claimed he had been told
OL,18,Fit was a jewellery store and said, "I
OL,19,Fwould never have set foot there if I
OL,20,Fhad known."
OL,26,@kD@SOk
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1783982881
OL,3,CMastermind behind E88m Louvre heist
OL,4,Cthought they 'could have stolen more'
OL,6,FDuring the interview with Ghelamallah
OL,7,FA, he claimed to have become annoyed
OL,8,Fat the speed at which Abdoulaye N was
OL,9,Fbreaking into the display cases,
OL,10,Fsaying: "If we take more than three
OL,11,Fminutes, we know we have to leave,
OL,12,Fotherwise we'll be reported. For me,
OL,13,Fwhat we did was taking too long."
OL,15,FIn total, they seized eight pieces of
OL,16,Fjewellery that had belonged to French
OL,17,Froyalty, estimated to contain more
OL,18,Fthan 8,500 precious stones and valued
OL,19,Fat over #75 million.
OL,26,@kD@SOk
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1783982881
OL,3,CMastermind behind E88m Louvre heist
OL,4,Cthought they 'could have stolen more'
OL,6,FThey dropped Empress Eugenie's crown
OL,7,Fduring their escape, which was found
OL,8,Fnear the Louvre, with Abdoulaye N
OL,9,Fadmitting it fell out of his bag.
OL,11,FLe Monde reports that investigators
OL,12,Fhave CCTV of Abdoulaye N handing over
OL,13,Fthe jewels at an underground car park
OL,14,Fin Aubervilliers in northern Paris,
OL,15,Fbut this is where their trail goes
OL,16,Fcold.
